The paper deals with algorithms for computing representative families of matroids, which are combinatorial objects studied in discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and graph theory (cs.GT). The applications of the approach include algorithms on graphs of bounded treewidth (cs.DS), which is a common topic in computational geometry (cs.CG) and combinatorics (cs.CC).
